<L>Black fire and horror &s;hot with equal rage</L>
<L>Among&s;t his angels&mdash;and his throne it&s;elf</L>
<L>Mixt with Tartarian &s;ulphur, and &s;trange fire;</L>
<L>His own invented torments&mdash;but perhaps</L>
<L>The way &s;eems difficult and &s;teep, to &s;cale</L>
<L>With adver&s;e wing again&s;t a higher foe&mdash;</L>
<L>Let &s;uch bethink them, if the &s;leepy drench</L>
<L>Of that forgetful lake benumb not &s;till,</L>
<L>That with our proper motion we a&s;cend</L>
<L>Up to our native &s;eat&mdash;de&s;cent and fall</L>
<L>To us are adver&s;e&mdash;Who but felt of late,</L>
<L>When our fierce foe hung on our broken rear,</L>
<L>In&s;ulting and pur&s;ued thro' the deep,</L>
